272
00:43:14.833 --> 00:43:17.825
It's close to a mountain.
fresh air.

273
00:43:18.833 --> 00:43:21.575
and some great people too.

274
00:43:27.250 --> 00:43:28.740
That's pretty.

275
00:43:28.833 --> 00:43:30.573
Who gave it for you?

276
00:43:31.750 --> 00:43:34.867
Sweetie. would you like a candy?

277
00:43:42.667 --> 00:43:45.739
Eun-hye. I told you not to
accept things from strangers.

278
00:43:46.042 --> 00:43:47.657
It's an expensive candy.

279
00:43:47.833 --> 00:43:49.664
Doesn't contain much sugar.

280
00:43:51.042 --> 00:43:53.033
You can have it.

281
00:43:53.167 --> 00:43:54.156
Let's go.

282
00:44:02.042 --> 00:44:03.623
Sweetie. stay on this side.

283
00:44:03.917 --> 00:44:05.202
Over here.

284
00:44:09.208 --> 00:44:10.323
What is it?

285
00:44:15.958 --> 00:44:17.289
My home...

286
00:44:19.625 --> 00:44:20.831
| live here.

287
00:44:29.625 --> 00:44:31.616
Are you in #407?

288
00:44:33.750 --> 00:44:35.661
We're neighbors?

289
00:44:35.833 --> 00:44:37.789
Moving in on the same day too?

290
00:44:38.917 --> 00:44:42.739
Are you moving in
without your husband?

291
00:44:42.917 --> 00:44:44.748
Are you divorced?

292
00:44:45.583 --> 00:44:46.823
Overseas business trip.

293
00:44:47.625 --> 00:44:49.911
Business trip?
On moving day?

294
00:44:50.625 --> 00:44:51.910
That's not right!

295
00:44:52.667 --> 00:44:53.907
Then why are you alone?

296
00:44:54.792 --> 00:44:57.704
My wife passed away
a few years ago.

297
00:44:59.792 --> 00:45:01.828
It's okay. you didn't
do it on purpose.

298
00:45:02.792 --> 00:45:03.907
I'm sorry.

299
00:45:04.833 --> 00:45:06.744
Let's go inside.

300
00:45:19.875 --> 00:45:20.864
One moment!

301
00:45:21.208 --> 00:45:22.038
Me?

302
00:45:22.667 --> 00:45:23.747
Pizza?

303
00:45:24.667 --> 00:45:25.622
Yes.

304
00:45:29.917 --> 00:45:31.578
Yes?

305
00:45:37.833 --> 00:45:38.788
What are you doing?

306
00:45:38.833 --> 00:45:40.619
I paid for that.

307
00:45:40.750 --> 00:45:41.660
What for?

308
00:45:41.708 --> 00:45:43.744
Pizza tastes great.

309
00:45:43.833 --> 00:45:45.949
but it's not nutritious
for the kids.

310
00:45:46.667 --> 00:45:51.582
So I was thinking of
making boiled chicken.

311
00:45:51.667 --> 00:45:52.907
if you like chicken...

312
00:45:53.583 --> 00:45:54.789
Do you like chicken?

313
00:45:56.583 --> 00:45:57.868
Good. that wasn't too bad.

314
00:45:58.583 --> 00:45:59.743
We're almost friends.

315
00:46:04.750 --> 00:46:05.705
What is it?

316
00:46:06.625 --> 00:46:08.707
Chief. I need a background check.

317
00:46:08.833 --> 00:46:10.573
Background check?

318
00:46:10.792 --> 00:46:13.750
There's a man next door.
something's off.

319
00:46:14.708 --> 00:46:16.869
Okay. I'll look into it.

320
00:46:20.917 --> 00:46:22.623
Jung Hyun—soo

321
00:46:23.583 --> 00:46:24.698
Chief. how was I?

322
00:46:24.792 --> 00:46:26.783
Doesn't it look like
she's into me?

323
00:46:26.917 --> 00:46:29.750
She asked for
your background check.

324
00:46:30.750 --> 00:46:32.581
She did what?

325
00:46:33.583 --> 00:46:35.869
It's because you
came onto her too hard.

326
00:46:36.792 --> 00:46:38.623
This is fieldwork.

327
00:46:38.708 --> 00:46:39.823
But she's at my doorstep.

328
00:46:39.917 --> 00:46:43.580
Don't joke around with
background check.

329
00:46:47.667 --> 00:46:48.702
Here.

330
00:46:51.625 --> 00:46:52.910
Why do you have this?

331
00:46:53.667 --> 00:46:56.625
Are you from Yanbian?

332
00:46:57.583 --> 00:47:00.780
She was Korean-Chinese.
How did you know?

333
00:47:01.750 --> 00:47:02.739
Nothing.

334
00:47:04.833 --> 00:47:06.949
Since we're neighbors.

335
00:47:07.667 --> 00:47:09.623
can I get your name?

336
00:47:11.833 --> 00:47:13.789
Yeon-soo. Chae Yeon-soo.

337
00:47:14.750 --> 00:47:15.830
I'm a 'soo' too.

338
00:47:15.958 --> 00:47:16.868
Pardon?

339
00:47:17.667 --> 00:47:19.578
Hyun-soo. Jung Hyun-soo.

340
00:47:19.833 --> 00:47:21.824
Chae Yeon-soo.
Jung Hyun-soo.

341
00:47:25.917 --> 00:47:27.873
2 neighborsoo!

342
00:47:32.792 --> 00:47:35.659
How's chicken soo-p for dinner?

343
00:47:40.667 --> 00:47:44.580
Jung Hyun-soo.
33-year old.

344
00:47:44.750 --> 00:47:47.822
works at Daesung Corp..
Development team.

345
00:47:48.792 --> 00:47:50.703
a widower of 3 years.

346
00:47:50.833 --> 00:47:52.619
Cause of death?

347
00:47:53.792 --> 00:47:55.578
Robbery. murder.

348
00:47:55.792 --> 00:47:56.656
What?

349
00:47:56.833 --> 00:47:59.620
She was pregnant at the time.

350
00:47:59.708 --> 00:48:02.666
He took 3 years off
and started working recently.

351
00:48:02.833 --> 00:48:05.791
he sold their home
and moved there.

352
00:48:13.875 --> 00:48:16.582
Does this go to
Hyehwa station?

353
00:48:16.708 --> 00:48:17.914
That's what it says.

354
00:48:18.667 --> 00:48:19.747
So it does.

355
00:48:21.208 --> 00:48:22.914
I left my wallet at home...

356
00:48:23.583 --> 00:48:25.619
Just hop on.
I won't charge you!

357
00:48:25.667 --> 00:48:26.656
For free?

358
00:48:26.750 --> 00:48:29.822
I need to buy lunch later too...

359
00:48:29.917 --> 00:48:31.873
And take a bus back home.

360
00:48:32.750 --> 00:48:33.660
I should run home.

361
00:48:33.708 --> 00:48:35.699
You can't even borrow
money at work?

362
00:48:35.792 --> 00:48:37.623
No. I'm a loner.

363
00:48:44.917 --> 00:48:46.657
Bye.

364
00:48:54.583 --> 00:48:55.914
- Say bye to mom.
- Bye-bye. mom.

365
00:49:15.917 --> 00:49:17.657
Rock. paper. scissors!

366
00:49:54.875 --> 00:49:56.581
Hyun-soo.

367
00:49:58.708 --> 00:50:00.664
Did you wait for me?

368
00:50:01.958 --> 00:50:02.913
I like it.

369
00:50:03.708 --> 00:50:04.663
What?

370
00:50:05.625 --> 00:50:08.583
I like to wait.

371
00:50:15.208 --> 00:50:16.698
Do you...

372
00:50:17.917 --> 00:50:19.908
like plays?

373
00:50:21.833 --> 00:50:23.664
Wait. are you...

374
00:50:23.958 --> 00:50:26.950
asking me out on a date?

375
00:50:27.750 --> 00:50:30.947
But you're married.
you really shouldn't.

376
00:50:31.667 --> 00:50:32.827
Actually.

377
00:50:32.958 --> 00:50:34.664
I'm in a play.

378
00:50:36.958 --> 00:50:38.869
You're an actress?

379
00:50:39.625 --> 00:50:41.866
No wonder.
you're so pretty.

380
00:50:41.917 --> 00:50:43.657
I'm the lead.

381
00:50:45.375 --> 00:50:46.740
Mommy!

382
00:50:46.833 --> 00:50:48.573
My princess!

383
00:50:48.708 --> 00:50:50.699
How did you know
I was coming?

384
00:50:50.833 --> 00:50:53.791
She said it was time
for you to come home.

385
00:50:53.917 --> 00:50:55.657
she was right on.

386
00:50:55.708 --> 00:50:58.666
Mommy. is he your boyfriend?

387
00:51:22.667 --> 00:51:23.782
Cobalt.

388
00:51:37.583 --> 00:51:41.701
After finding out that you're alive.
I couldn't do anything.

389
00:51:42.875 --> 00:51:46.868
You still haven't
changed a bit.

390
00:51:48.750 --> 00:51:53.574
I can't get it out of my head.
your acting.

391
00:51:54.375 --> 00:51:55.660
Was it bad?

392
00:51:55.750 --> 00:51:59.698
Not at all!
It was good. Really good!

393
00:52:01.583 --> 00:52:03.790
It feels like I get to
become a different person.

394
00:52:03.917 --> 00:52:05.873
when I'm up on stage.

395
00:52:13.875 --> 00:52:15.786
That tie suits you.

396
00:52:15.833 --> 00:52:17.619
Oh... Yeah?

397
00:52:17.917 --> 00:52:20.750
It was a gift from my wife.

398
00:52:21.792 --> 00:52:26.582
My husband has a similar
cobalt necktie.

399
00:52:27.583 --> 00:52:28.823
I gave it to him.

400
00:52:44.625 --> 00:52:45.910
I love this color.

401
00:52:46.917 --> 00:52:51.616
I wanted to tie it myself
on our wedding day.

402
00:52:52.958 --> 00:52:54.789
Alright. boss.

403
00:52:55.875 --> 00:52:58.582
I got work in Seoul.
so I'll head over first.

404
00:52:58.667 --> 00:53:00.578
Good. take care.

405
00:53:00.875 --> 00:53:02.831
You won't stay
for the wedding?

406
00:53:02.917 --> 00:53:04.908
You'll be in Seoul
for your honeymoon.

407
00:53:05.667 --> 00:53:08.625
l'll head over first
and set things up.

408
00:53:45.708 --> 00:53:47.619
Mister. look at that!

409
00:53:59.167 --> 00:54:00.657
Not gonna eat?

410
00:54:01.625 --> 00:54:04.742
Let's live a normal life.

411
00:54:11.667 --> 00:54:12.656
Yes?

412
00:54:14.750 --> 00:54:15.739
What?

413
00:54:17.750 --> 00:54:18.739
I understand.

414
00:54:21.708 --> 00:54:22.868
Something wrong?

415
00:54:23.792 --> 00:54:26.909
Chun-mo's been kidnapped.
go back to the hotel.

416
00:54:27.583 --> 00:54:28.663
I'll come with you.

417
00:54:28.750 --> 00:54:30.581
It's our honeymoon.

418
00:54:30.958 --> 00:54:33.574
Listen to me
and head back.

419
00:55:02.583 --> 00:55:03.572
Yes?

420
00:55:04.750 --> 00:55:08.698
Joong-sang told me
not to tell you.

421
00:55:09.583 --> 00:55:13.826
We tracked your father's
real killer.

422
00:55:13.917 --> 00:55:15.908
and he asked me
to take care of it.

423
00:55:16.792 --> 00:55:19.659
But when l was taken hostage.

424
00:55:19.833 --> 00:55:21.744
he tried to rescue me...

425
00:55:21.833 --> 00:55:23.698
Where are they?

426
00:55:24.958 --> 00:55:26.744
Tell me!

427
00:55:32.708 --> 00:55:34.664
I had so much fun today.

428
00:55:38.750 --> 00:55:40.741
I know it's wrong.

429
00:55:42.583 --> 00:55:48.579
but for a second. I wished
you weren't married.

430
00:56:03.958 --> 00:56:04.913
Mrs. Chae?

431
00:56:05.667 --> 00:56:06.622
Yes. ma'am?

432
00:56:06.708 --> 00:56:07.914
Eun-hye is asleep.

433
00:56:08.583 --> 00:56:10.915
I got a feast to prepare.
l have to go home.

434
00:56:11.625 --> 00:56:14.822
I'm almost there.
could you wait a bit?

435
00:56:16.625 --> 00:56:17.614
Okay.

436
00:56:17.792 --> 00:56:20.579
Sir. could you stop the cab?

437
00:56:20.833 --> 00:56:22.824
There's still a way to go.

438
00:56:24.792 --> 00:56:29.661
It'd be awkward if your babysitter
saw us together again.

439
00:56:32.917 --> 00:56:33.906
Hyun-soo!

440
00:56:34.750 --> 00:56:35.830
Go ahead.

441
00:57:15.875 --> 00:57:17.831
l have something to tell you.

442
00:57:18.958 --> 00:57:20.789
To be honest.

443
00:57:21.583 --> 00:57:23.574
my husband passed away.

444
00:57:24.917 --> 00:57:26.748
I already knew.

445
00:57:27.667 --> 00:57:28.952
But how?

446
00:57:29.833 --> 00:57:34.907
You're an amazing actress.

447
00:57:36.667 --> 00:57:38.749
but a terrible liar.

448
00:58:06.583 --> 00:58:06.912
I'm sorry.

449
00:58:07.583 --> 00:58:09.665
No. I'm okay.

450
00:58:45.292 --> 00:58:46.702
Don't answer.

451
00:58:47.833 --> 00:58:50.791
I'm sorry.
it's an urgent call.

452
00:58:57.875 --> 00:58:58.910
Yes?

453
00:59:12.917 --> 00:59:14.908
A colleague got into
an accident.

454
00:59:15.875 --> 00:59:18.582
and is en route
to the hospital.

455
00:59:19.917 --> 00:59:21.623
Hyun-soo.

456
00:59:21.875 --> 00:59:25.697
Could you sleep here
just for tonight?

457
00:59:25.833 --> 00:59:27.869
Eun-hye will be alone.

458
00:59:29.792 --> 00:59:31.908
Don't worry.
be safe.

459
00:59:43.750 --> 00:59:44.785
Sook-hee!

460
00:59:46.333 --> 00:59:47.288
Min-ju!

461
00:59:48.667 --> 00:59:49.747
Why are you here?

462
00:59:49.833 --> 00:59:50.913
Isn't it obvious?

463
00:59:52.667 --> 00:59:53.907
I got my first mission.

464
00:59:54.625 --> 00:59:55.785
Your Southern accent is gone.

465
00:59:55.833 --> 00:59:56.697
Of course.

466
00:59:56.792 --> 00:59:58.908
When I discharge.
I'll be living in Seoul.

467
00:59:59.667 --> 01:00:01.783
Seoul must be
treating you well.

468
01:00:04.625 --> 01:00:05.831
You got a man?

469
01:00:05.875 --> 01:00:07.911
You do. don't you? Tell me!

470
01:00:08.667 --> 01:00:09.656
Of course not.

471
01:00:09.750 --> 01:00:11.786
You can't fool me.

472
01:00:23.750 --> 01:00:24.705
Hey.

473
01:00:24.833 --> 01:00:26.744
Why's the mood so weird?

474
01:00:27.708 --> 01:00:28.914
This is all wrong.

475
01:00:29.625 --> 01:00:30.785
l'll undress you.

476
01:00:31.625 --> 01:00:32.580
Very good.

477
01:00:32.750 --> 01:00:35.583
Drinking isn't the only thing
I came here for.

478
01:00:37.875 --> 01:00:38.910
Come here. baby.

479
01:00:39.583 --> 01:00:40.868
Let me feel you.

480
01:00:41.708 --> 01:00:43.573
I think I'm drunk.

481
01:00:43.667 --> 01:00:44.907
What are you doing?

482
01:00:46.583 --> 01:00:47.572
One second.

483
01:00:47.792 --> 01:00:48.702
Why?

484
01:00:48.833 --> 01:00:50.664
Washroom...

485
01:00:52.208 --> 01:00:53.914
Come on.
hurry up.

486
01:00:55.542 --> 01:00:56.873
Conﬂnue.

487
01:00:57.792 --> 01:00:59.828
Take that off.
finish undressing.

488
01:01:13.750 --> 01:01:15.661
Did you take my phone?

489
01:01:17.958 --> 01:01:20.574
l'll return it.
let her go.

490
01:01:22.792 --> 01:01:25.750
You must've made a copy.

491
01:01:26.625 --> 01:01:27.660
Give it.

492
01:02:09.667 --> 01:02:10.747
Fucking bitch!

493
01:02:21.750 --> 01:02:23.706
Min-ju. are you alright?

494
01:03:01.583 --> 01:03:02.948
Get her to the ER!

495
01:03:04.792 --> 01:03:06.703
She lost too much blood!

496
01:03:06.833 --> 01:03:08.664
Flash drive.

497
01:03:10.750 --> 01:03:12.661
- Start hacking.
- Yes. ma'am.

498
01:03:18.750 --> 01:03:19.785
We can't do it here.

499
01:03:19.917 --> 01:03:21.657
Go to the ER!

500
01:03:21.875 --> 01:03:22.955
Let's head back.

501
01:03:24.667 --> 01:03:26.749
Min-ju'll die!
She'll die like this!

502
01:03:26.792 --> 01:03:27.827
And why's that?!

503
01:03:30.833 --> 01:03:34.576
You should've done
your job properly.

504
01:04:31.917 --> 01:04:33.657
Yeon-soo. you okay?

505
01:04:51.625 --> 01:04:53.581
Let it all out.

506
01:05:08.667 --> 01:05:10.658
Choi Chun-mo who emerged
during this op.

507
01:05:10.917 --> 01:05:13.875
is known as
a mid-level boss

508
01:05:14.667 --> 01:05:17.739
for a contract killer organization.

509
01:05:17.833 --> 01:05:20.905
and controls over
5 mid-size subsidiaries.

510
01:05:21.375 --> 01:05:23.741
Using data from our hard drive.

511
01:05:23.917 --> 01:05:26.579
Choi became a major player.

512
01:05:26.667 --> 01:05:30.660
and his pawn Sook-hee
was recruited to the agency?

513
01:05:31.750 --> 01:05:33.706
Isn't that fishy?

514
01:05:34.750 --> 01:05:35.739
Wait a minute.

515
01:05:35.917 --> 01:05:38.750
then she's been
a double agent?

516
01:05:39.667 --> 01:05:43.580
We've put an agent to watch her.
and there haven't been any issues.

517
01:05:43.917 --> 01:05:49.742
Choi is someone who eliminated
her husband to reach his level.

518
01:05:49.833 --> 01:05:51.744
Enough about his
back story.

519
01:05:51.833 --> 01:05:54.825
we need to catch his
puppet master.

520
01:05:54.917 --> 01:05:58.830
We've received intel that
they'll contact HlN.

521
01:05:58.958 --> 01:06:00.664
We'll move in then.

522
01:06:00.750 --> 01:06:03.583
Why don't we assign her?

523
01:06:10.625 --> 01:06:12.832
Did you make mom cry?

524
01:06:13.750 --> 01:06:15.581
I... didn't...

525
01:06:15.792 --> 01:06:17.828
l consoled her.

526
01:06:18.583 --> 01:06:20.790
What does that mean?

527
01:06:20.917 --> 01:06:22.657
Consoling is.

528
01:06:22.750 --> 01:06:27.574
when you cry.
I say "don't cry."

529
01:06:27.750 --> 01:06:30.787
Can you console mommy?

530
01:06:31.583 --> 01:06:32.572
What do you mean?

531
01:06:32.792 --> 01:06:35.579
When mommy cries.

532
01:06:36.875 --> 01:06:41.665
you say.
"don't cry. don't cry."

533
01:06:45.833 --> 01:06:47.573
You're up?

534
01:06:47.667 --> 01:06:48.907
Sit down.
food's getting cold.

535
01:06:49.583 --> 01:06:52.780
I'm full.
and sleepy.

536
01:07:05.583 --> 01:07:07.665
Did she bug you?

537
01:07:07.792 --> 01:07:08.952
She said.

538
01:07:10.083 --> 01:07:12.790
I should console you
whenever you cry.

539
01:07:13.750 --> 01:07:15.615
Can I do that?

540
01:07:16.917 --> 01:07:19.829
The me that you know

541
01:07:21.458 --> 01:07:22.868
isn't the real me.

542
01:07:24.583 --> 01:07:26.699
That's what
I wanted to tell you.

543
01:07:27.250 --> 01:07:28.581
What?

544
01:07:28.917 --> 01:07:32.830
I'm not the person
you think you know.

545
01:07:33.750 --> 01:07:35.615
I'm a terrible person.

546
